Ghana Cocoa Board Calls an ‘Emergency Meeting’ With Coffee Buyers in Accra

-- B y   A l a s t a i r   R e e d
-- 
2011-07-15T09:54:00Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-07-15/ghana-cocoa-board-calls-an-emergency-meeting-with-coffee-buyers-in-accra.html
The Ghana Cocoa Board called an
“emergency meeting” with licensed coffee buyers in the West
African nation to discuss the revitalization of the coffee
industry.  The meeting will be held in Accra on July 20 at 10 a.m.
local time, Cocobod, as the board is known, said in an e-mailed
statement today.  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Alastair Reed at 
 areed12@bloomberg.net  